      "message": "I\u0027m still not sure what this patch is trying to accomplish.  The commit message goes directly into \"what\" without talking about the why at all, which is arguably more important.  The patchset itself is making lots of changes to core existing data structures and I really have no idea why.  I can\u0027t figure out why you made those changes unless you put that in the commit message.  Before you send your next patch, lets get what you\u0027re trying to accomplish laid out.\n\nI can\u0027t find any description of SNI where setting a hardcoded fixed hostname would be correct usage.  If there\u0027s a standard I\u0027m not aware of that specifies a hostname of \"mtls\" please add it to your commit message",
