      "writtenOn": "2026-04-07T23:03:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e @ed@tanous.net\n\u003e The SERVER context (getSslServerContext) is only modified and , \n\u003e not the client context (getSSLClientContext).\n\nThe server context is used for the server.  the client context is used for aggregation.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e The dual context is needed because:\n\u003e - Satellite BMCs connect TO the aggregator (server role) for registration\n\u003e - Aggregator connects TO satellites (client role) for data collection\n\u003e \n\u003e Both directions use mTLS, but the server role needs to also support \n\nTHere\u0027s not \"both directions\" in aggregation connections.  Aggregation makes GET requests to the satellite.  \n\n\u003e HTTPS for HMC/GUI clients, hence the dual context.\n\u003e \n\u003e SNI-Based Context Selection:\n\u003e \n\u003e The client (satellite BMC) sets SNI hostname to \"mtls.bmc\" before\n\u003e connecting (in http_client.hpp). This SNI value is transmitted in\n\u003e the TLS Client Hello message.\n\u003e \n\u003e The server (aggregator BMC) examines the SNI in clientHelloCallback()\n\u003e and switches to the appropriate SSL context:\n\u003e - SNI\u003d\"mtls.bmc\" → mTLS context (require client certificate)\n\u003e - Any other SNI → HTTPS context (no client certificate)\n\u003e \n\u003e \n\u003e Client-side changes (http_client.hpp):\n\u003e - Set SNI to \"mtls.bmc\" for aggregation connections, before connection\n\u003e - Already implemented in existing code\n\u003e \n\u003e Server-side changes (ssl_key_handler.cpp, ssl_dual_context.hpp):\n\u003e - Dual SSL contexts (HTTPS + mTLS)\n\u003e - SNI-based context switching in clientHelloCallback()\n\u003e - This patch implements the server-side changes",
      "parentUuid": "27e9c170_2088c240",
